"As mobile devices have become key to the enterprise, the question of how best to secure them is hotly debated. Many enterprises have introduced remote disabling or wiping of devices, sometimes combining the two. But as employees increasingly use their own personal smart devices for work, often as part of a raft of mobile devices ranging from laptops through tablets to phones, the task of setting up remote disabling facilities across the enterprise can become Sisyphean. Tracey Caldwell reports on the technologies and solutions available for remote disabling of devices and the issues and considerations around remote disabling. The compromise between security and the ideal of the mobile enterprise is different for every business and is emerging as very much a business as well as a technological issue."
